 origin): dissimilated form of   Berringer  . Compare   Benninger  .","German: habitational name for someone from a place called Belling or Bellingen (see   Belling  ). It is also found in France (Lorraine).","Americanized form of French <b>Bélanger</b> (see   Belanger  ) or of its variant   Bellanger  . Compare   Ballinger   2 and   Bellenger   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Berringer","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): from the Anglo-Norman French personal name <i>Berenger</i>, an Old French form of ancient Germanic <i>Beringar</i>, <i>Barengar</i>, composed of the elements <i>ber(n)</i> ‘bear’ + <i>gair</i> ‘spear’. The surname has several variants, including   Beringer  ,   Barringer  , and   Banger  , as well as the dissimilated forms   Bellanger  ,   Bellinger  ,   Ballanger  , and   Ballinger  , where /l/ has been substituted for /r/. The personal name <i>Berenger</i> was well known in England in the 12th and 13th centuries, having been borne by one of the paladins in the widely popular Charlemagne romances.","German: variant of   Beringer  .","Americanized form of German   Boehringer  ."]},{"name":"Ballenger","meanings":["English (of Norman origin; Gloucestershire): variant of   Bellinger   (see also   Ballinger  ). Compare   Ballanger   2 and   Bellenger   2.","French: variant of   Bellanger   1 and, in North America, (also) an altered form of this. This form of the surname is almost extinct in France. Compare   Ballanger   1 and   Bellenger   1."]}]},{"name":"Catarina","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Portuguese and Spanish: from the personal name <i>Catarino</i>, male form of <i>Catarina</i> (see   Catherine  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Catherine","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Katherine .  This form of the name is also used in France."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Catarina Bellinger was christened on 22 October 1632, in Württemberg, Germany as the daughter of Johannes Bellingers and Mrs 